{"id": 7017, "title": "Ticket #7017: condor_master can't be run as pid 1 inside a container", "description": "<blockquote>\nUsers would like to run condor inside a docker or other container, but there is an explicit check in the procd that prevent the procd, and thus condor from running when the master is pid 1.  Turns out this check was only needed with privsep, which is no longer supported.  Let's remove this check from the procd, and make it easer for user to run condor inside containers.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2019-May-20 15:14:34 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW</strong>: Looks good!</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-May-16 07:09</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/5bbfad3b07ab0847cc3681bf24706c57fd2771d6\">[56895]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7017\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7017'); return false;\" title=\"condor_master can't be run as pid 1 inside a container\">#7017</a></span> Committer: Tim Theisen  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-May-15 11:21</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/99e8bb4ef4140a211428e4742f7aad5c9533c51b\">[56883]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7017\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7017'); return false;\" title=\"condor_master can't be run as pid 1 